{
  "texts": [
    "OpenAI was an early pioneer of LLM use policies, emphasizing legal compliance and protection of privacy (OpenAI, 2023b (OpenAI,, 2024 (OpenAI,, 2023c,d),d), and along these ends, has employed both red teaming and guardrailing to prevent users from soliciting various kinds of harmful responses from their models (OpenAI, 2023e).",
    "Meta, as a large-scale social media platform, addresses risks such as election interference in their use policies (Meta, 2024a; Meta, 2024b Meta,, 2023).",
    "Anthropic's policies emphasize ethical alignment in particular (Anthropic, 2023a (Anthropic,, 2022;; Anthropic, 2024 Anthropic,, 2023b)), and they employ guardrailing and red teaming practices and fairness evaluations to develop models with unbiased decision-making capacities.",
    "In this section, we categorize and describe various strategies for attacking LLMs.",
    "Our analysis reflects the reality that the LLM's attack surface is high context-dependent and influenced by many factors including target-system type, its infrastructure, conversational history, and access privileges."
  ]
}